title: Household income of white families in the U.S. 1990 to 2018
yAxis: Median income in 2018 CPI-U-RS adjusted U.S. dollars
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Median income in 2018 CPI-U-RS adjusted U.S. dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 29.
In general Median income in 2018 CPI-U-RS adjusted U.S. dollars has rose over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2016 and 2017.
Maximum Median income in 2018 CPI-U-RS adjusted U.S. dollars, about 70642.0 was reported at Year 2018
The lowest Median income in 2018 CPI-U-RS adjusted U.S. dollars, of value 55568.0 was reported at Year 1991
